LEARNING DAX PART 2: FILTER CONTEXT

SUMX(
         Sales,  - SUMX iterate only the rows in Sales that visible in the current filter context
         Sales[Quantity] * Sales[Net Price]
)


Power BI matrix creates filter context - a filter on the model (e.g. Brand) => then computer the measure

The filter context can be created by Power BI - a filter that exists around your code

The filter context is the filter that placed on the model and mostly is created by the visual by Power BI, and is follows the relationships


Filter context is a table, it is a set of filters that contains one or more tables, each filter correspond to a table in the filter context





